        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(plugins): prevent bundled plugin paths from being written to plugins.load.paths",
        "body": "Fixes #85334\n\nThis PR addresses the circular doctor warning loop by preventing bundled plugin paths from being written to `plugins.load.paths` across **all three code paths** that previously added them:\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. `src/plugins/update.ts` - syncPluginsForUpdateChannel (2 call sites)\n- Removed `loadHelpers.addPath(bundledInfo.localPath)` calls\n- Bundled plugins are auto-loaded by discovery; explicit load paths trigger doctor warnings and create update/doctor churn cycles\n\n### 2. `src/commands/onboarding-plugin-install.ts` - addPluginLoadPath\n- Added bundled path guard that checks if the path being added is a bundled plugin path and skips adding it to `plugins.load.paths`\n- Uses the same bundled plugin detection logic as doctor repair\n\n### 3. `src/commands/doctor/repair-sequencing.ts`\n- Moved `maybeRepairBundledPluginLoadPaths` to run **last**, after all other repairs that might write to `plugins.load.paths` (e.g., `repairMissingConfiguredPluginInstalls`)\n\n## Result\n\nWith all three writers covered, `doctor --fix` is now truly idempotent and will not re-add bundled paths that it just removed.\n\n## Tests\n\n- ✅ All existing `src/plugins/update.test.ts` tests pass (79/79)\n- Updated test expectations to reflect the new behavior where bundled paths are no longer added during channel sync\n\n## Verification\n\nTested on production gateway (macOS, npm global install):\n- `openclaw update` no longer adds bundled paths to `plugins.load.paths`\n- `openclaw doctor --fix` removes any existing bundled paths and they stay removed\n- No circular warning loop\n\n---\n\nThis PR complements #85358 by covering the `update.ts` sync writer that was identified as missing in the ClawSweeper review.",
